records.addlTxt:
2:58 PM; Case called for Plea/sentencing hearing.  Defendant James E Szocs in court.  Attorney Justin G Griffis in court for James E Szocs.  Prosecuting attorney Molly M Schmidt in court for the State of Wisconsin. Atty. Griffis advises parties are prepared to proceed today and files the plea questionnaire.  Court reviews the document and recite the offer as listed in the document.  State and Defense confirm the offer.  Court conducts plea colloquy with the defendant. Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1, Court finds defendant guilty. 

Sentencing arguments made by the State.
Sentencing arguments made by Atty. Griffis.


COUNT 1:
The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

30 Days Jail Straight Time.

Term of Probation: 12 Months

Conditions of Probation:
-	Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
-	Follow any conditions deemed appropriate by Agent;
-	No violent contact with Victim A listed in the Criminal Complaint;
-	Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.'s;
-	No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
-	No use or possession of any controlled substances without a valid doctor's prescription
-	Make best efforts to Maintain/Obtain full time employment;
-	Defendant is not to possess any dangerous weapons.

COSTS:  $100.00 (Court only ordered the DV surcharge and waived all other court costs);

DNA Surcharge: $200.00;

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

Total costs/fine/forfeiture:  to be paid as a condition of probation. Failure to pay;  will result in a civil judgment.
